                <div class="detailed-view-card-container">
                    <h1 class="detailed-view-card-heading">srisailam</h1>
                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">Srisailam is a renowned Hindu pilgrimage town and a significant cultural center in the state of Andhra Pradesh, India, famous for being home to the Mallikarjuna Jyotirlinga Temple, one of the twelve Jyotirlingas of Lord Shiva, and the Sri Bhramaramba Ammavari Shakti Peetham, a revered Shakti Peetham. Situated on the banks of the River Krishna, it is a major center for both Shaivism and Shaktism traditions within Hinduism. The town also features other points of interest, including the Pathala Ganga Walkway.</p>
