                <div class="detailed-view-card-container">
                    <h1 class="detailed-view-card-heading">Mysore Palace</h1>
                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">The Mysore Palace, also known as Amba Vilas Palace, is a historic and magnificent royal residence in the city of Mysuru, Karnataka, India, renowned for its distinctive Indo-Saracenic architecture and elaborate design by architect Henry Irwin. This current structure, completed in 1912, stands as the fourth palace on the site, with previous versions destroyed by fire, lightning, and demolition. Visitors are drawn to the palace's impressive grey granite exterior, which features an Indo-Saracenic style with prominent square towers and colorful domes, while its interior boasts ornate marble floors, intricate murals, and a famous Golden Throne. The palace is especially vibrant on Sundays, public holidays.</p>
